title: Open Shell in a Kubernetes Node
tags: @zettel _method k8s
roam-id: 651dbd64-822b-4285-8cb5-004304dfdae1
type: text/markdown

- you can directly connect into a pod with the following command

  ``` bash
  kubectl debug node/${NODE_NAME} -it --image=busybox
  ```

- or with a plugin install <https://github.com/kvaps/kubectl-node-shell>

- do

  ``` shell
  kubectl get node
  ```

  ``` example
  NAME                                                  STATUS   ROLES    AGE   VERSION
  gke-bird-pretest-gke-bird-pretest-gke-8045da2c-be3z   Ready    <none>   25d   v1.34.1-gke.1829001
  gke-bird-pretest-gke-bird-pretest-gke-8045da2c-e30d   Ready    <none>   25d   v1.34.1-gke.1829001
  gke-bird-pretest-gke-bird-pretest-gke-8045da2c-ja35   Ready    <none>   25d   v1.34.1-gke.1829001
  gke-bird-pretest-gke-bird-pretest-gke-8045da2c-t5fw   Ready    <none>   25d   v1.34.1-gke.1829001
  gke-bird-pretest-gke-bird-pretest-gke-8045da2c-ztsc   Ready    <none>   25d   v1.34.1-gke.1829001
  ```

- exec into one of them

  ``` shell
  kubectl node-shell gke-bird-pretest-gke-bird-pretest-gke-8045da2c-be3z
  ```
